theorem dense_iff_closure_interior_closure_eq_univ
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Dense (A : Set X) ↔ closure (interior (closure (A : Set X))) = Set.univ := by
  classical
  constructor
  · intro hDense
    exact Topology.closure_interior_closure_eq_univ_of_dense (A := A) hDense
  · intro hEq
    -- `closure (interior (closure A))` is contained in `closure A`.
    have hIncl :
        closure (interior (closure (A : Set X))) ⊆ closure (A : Set X) := by
      have hIntSub :
          interior (closure (A : Set X)) ⊆ closure (A : Set X) :=
        interior_subset
      exact closure_mono hIntSub
    -- Hence `univ ⊆ closure A`.
    have hUnivSubset : (Set.univ : Set X) ⊆ closure (A : Set X) := by
      simpa [hEq] using hIncl
    -- Equality of closures follows.
    have hClosureEq : closure (A : Set X) = Set.univ := by
      apply Set.Subset.antisymm
      · intro _ _; trivial
      · exact hUnivSubset
    -- Translate to density.
    exact
      (Topology.dense_iff_closure_eq_univ (A := A)).2 hClosureEq
